MyGov.be: Digital government at your fingertips!

Discover the practical and secure app from the Belgian government. Thanks to this official app, you always have access to your personal data, administrative documents, certificates and requests, wherever you are.

With just one click, you can access a wide range of government services and official documents, as well as your 'My eBox', all available in mobile format. This app also serves as a digital wallet. It can be used to store all kinds of documents.

Thanks to this online service, you can now contact the authorities directly and request certificates via the app. No more paperwork and queuing down at the town hall!

Download the Belgian government app MyGov.be  now and discover a simpler, more secure way of managing your administrative records.

My bpost app: easily track, receive, or send parcels and registered mail 
 
■ Never lose track of a parcel, including deliveries from PostNL, DPD, DHL, and other carriers – whenever, wherever. Automatically track your bpost parcels, or scan or enter the barcode of the parcel you want to follow. 
 
■ Not at home at the expected delivery time? Let us know via your delivery preferences where we can deliver your bpost parcel, or easily postpone the delivery by a day. 
 
■ Set your delivery preference for registered mail. Let us know who is authorized to receive your registered mail, or choose to have it delivered directly to your letterbox. Would you prefer to receive your mail a day later, or pick it up immediately at a Post Office or Postal Point? Just let us know 
 
■ Sending a parcel? Quickly create a shipping label in the app and print it at home, at a Post Office, or Post Point.  
 
■ Need to send registered mail? Easily create your own shipping label for your registered mail. Print yourself or go to a Post Office or Post Point and have it printed for you. Affix it to your envelope and pop it in the post! 
 
■ Open Parcel Lockers without a screen via the app. 
 
■ Choose when you receive notifications for parcels and registered mail. 
 
■ Expecting a parcel from outside the EU? Then pay the import costs securely via the app. This way you can be sure that the request is coming from bpost and protect yourself against phishing. 
 
■ Find Pick-up points & Drop-off points. With 3,100+ Post Offices, Post Points, Parcel Points and Parcel Lockers, you’ll always find one close by.

Use the UK ETA app to apply for an electronic travel authorisation (ETA) to come to the UK.

Who can apply

Find out if you need an ETA to travel to the UK at: https://www.gov.uk/electronic-travel-authorisation. 

How to apply on the UK ETA app
1. Take a photo of your passport.
2. Scan the chip in your passport.
3. Scan your face.
4. Take a photo of yourself.
5. Answer some questions about yourself.
6. Pay for your application.

It should only take 10 minutes to apply.

You do not need to enter your travel details.

Before you start

To apply you will need:

• an iPhone 8 or newer with IOS 16 or later
• the passport you will use to travel to the UK
• a credit card, debit card or Apple Pay
• access to your emails

If you're applying for someone else they must be with you. If they are not, you should apply online at: https://www.gov.uk/electronic-travel-authorisation.

If you need to travel soon
You must apply for an ETA before you travel to the UK. You can travel to the UK while waiting for a decision. 

After you apply
You'll usually get a decision within 3 working days, but you may get a quicker decision. Occasionally, it may take longer than 3 working days. 

If your ETA is approved, we'll link this to the passport you applied with. You must use this passport to travel to the UK. 

Privacy and security

The app is safe and secure. No information is stored on the app or your phone after you close it. You can delete the app after you have completed your application.

For information on staying safe online visit the UK Cyber Aware website: https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/cyberaware/home

Accessibility
You can read our accessibility statement at: https://confirm-your-identity.homeoffice.gov.uk/register/eta-app-accessibility

Google Authenticator adds an extra layer of security to your online accounts by adding a second step of verification when you sign in. This means that in addition to your password, you'll also need to enter a code that is generated by the Google Authenticator app on your phone.

The verification code can be generated by the Google Authenticator app on your phone, even if you don't have a network or mobile connection.

• Sync your Authenticator codes to your Google Account and across your devices. This way, you can always access them even if you lose your phone.

• Set up your Authenticator accounts automatically with a QR code. This is quick and easy, and it helps to ensure that your codes are set up correctly.

• Support for multiple accounts. You can use the authenticator app to manage multiple accounts, so you don't have to switch between apps every time you need to sign in.

• Support for time-based and counter-based code generation. You can choose the type of code generation that best suits your needs.

• Transfer accounts between devices with a QR code. This is a convenient way to move your accounts to a new device.


To use Google Authenticator with Google, you need to enable 2-Step Verification on your Google Account. To get started, visit http://www.google.com/2step

• Reload your prepaid card or that of someone close to you
• Shift from a prepaid card to a subscription in just a few clicks 
• Activate, adapt or deactivate options
• Manage the tariff plans and options of members of your household included on your invoice
• Consult your advantages and accept your gifts available thanks to the Orange Thank You loyalty programme
• Add cards to your subscription for members of your household directly from the app
• Add an Internet or TV offer to your subscription
• Purchase a new smartphone and benefit from advantageous reductions by combining subscription + smartphone
• Find the nearest Orange shop
• Test the network coverage and speed of your internet connection 
• Access FAQs, web forms and useful numbers for contacting us. We will be delighted to assist you!

IMPORTANT INFORMATION

• Do not worry about your surf volume:
The use of the app itself is free in Belgium and abroad. 
The use of third-party applications is not: the use of GPS for the localization of Orange shops and the payment or reloading via a banking app is charged as a surfing volume.

• Use via mobile network or Wi-Fi:
The My Orange app is accessible via the mobile network or Wi-Fi.
Connecting through the app with our 3G/4G gives you immediate and automatic access to the app. 

Careful! For the automatic recognition to work, you may not use VPN or old proxy settings.
If you still need to enter your mobile phone number even if you’re using Orange's mobile network, you have to remove the proxy from the internet settings of your mobile device. More information at https://www.orange.be/nl/instellingen (Dutch) or https://www.orange.be/fr/parametres (French)

If you prefer connecting through Wi-Fi upon first usage after download or update, you’ll be asked to enter your phone number. The received SMS code will give you access to the app.

• Consumption view:
The information shown is limited to the card for which the application is used. 
Shown data is purely informative and does not replace your invoice.

BUSINESS OR CORPORATE CUSTOMER? 

• The My Orange app has also been optimized for our B2B customers with a SHAPE tariff. 
• Please contact your Fleet Manager if you have another business tariff plan. Together with the dedicated Customer Service we'll surely find a way to manage your consumption.

More information can be found on www.orange.be/myorange

Ben je Eneco-klant én heb je een digitale meter? Krijg échte inzichten in je energieverbruik dankzij de Eneco Smart Meter app. We laten je precies zien hoeveel je verbruikt en wat dat kost. Bovendien kom je te weten of je nu meer energie met wassen, verwarmen of koken verbruikt. Met het maandbudget hou je controle over je energiekosten. Wij berekenen of je goed bezig bent op basis van je echte verbruik.

We blijven de app ontwikkelen en verbeteren en komen snel met meer updates.

My Luminus is een app om snel en duidelijk een overzicht te geven van je energieverbruik. Heb je een digitale meter, dan volg je met de app je verbruik op per maand, week, en zelfs per dag; in kWh én in €. Je berekent en kiest op basis van die gegevens makkelijk je ideale voorschotbedrag. My Luminus bundelt ook al je Luminus-documenten en -klantgegevens op één handige plaats. 
Met de gratis My Luminus app kan je:
•	Energie besparen door je verbruik op te volgen. Nog geen digitale meter? Geef je meterstanden regelmatig door voor de nauwkeurigste weergave. Wel al een digitale meter? Via My Luminus krijg je toegang tot al je digitale verbruiksgegevens voor elektriciteit en gas. Je ziet wat je dagelijks aan elektriciteit en/of gas verbruikt en hoeveel dat kost - per dag, week, maand of jaar. Ook de injectie van je zonnepanelen volg je op de voet met My Luminus. Het enige wat je hoeft te doen is toestemming geven aan Fluvius.
•	Op basis van je meterstanden je ideale voorschot berekenen én aanpassen. Op die manier vermijd je een verrassing op je jaarafrekening. 
•	Je energiefacturen raadplegen en downloaden. 
•	Alle info over je energiecontract(en) terugvinden: je type tarief, de looptijd en prijs, het moment van de meteropname  en de (getrouwheids)kortingen waarop je recht hebt. Verder zie je welke andere Luminus-diensten je hebt geactiveerd. Wil je veranderen van tarief? Ook dat doe je in enkele kliks. 
•	Je contactgegevens en -voorkeuren en betalingswijze aanpassen.
•	Het antwoord vinden op al je vragen. We beantwoorden alle meestgestelde vragen in de app, of contacteer eenvoudig de klantendienst. 
•	Gebruik maken van de Extras-klantvoordelen. Via het heldere overzicht benut je snel alle kortingen en aanbiedingen.
